text: Introduction
label: root

text: Research on adult - learned second language ( L2 ) has provided considerable insight into the neurocognitive mechanisms underlying the learning and processing of L2 grammar [ 1 ] – [ 11 ] .
label: nsubj case compound punct amod amod nmod punct appos punct aux root amod obj case det amod nmod acl det obj cc conj case compound nmod punct dep punct case punct nmod punct punct

text: Of interest here , studies suggest that , despite the difficulties in acquiring L2 grammar , adult learners can approximate native - like levels of use and neurocognitive processing [ 12 ] – [ 15 ] .
label: case obl advmod punct nsubj root mark punct case det obl mark acl compound obj punct amod nsubj aux ccomp compound punct amod obj case nmod cc amod conj punct dep punct case punct nmod punct punct

text: However , it is not enough to have attained such native - like levels .
label: advmod punct expl cop advmod root mark aux csubj amod compound punct amod obj punct

text: Crucially , it is also desirable to retain them , even in the absence of continued practice or exposure to the L2 .
label: advmod punct expl cop advmod root mark csubj obj punct advmod case det obl case amod nmod cc conj case det nmod punct

text: In fact , substantial periods ( months to years ) of limited or no exposure following L2 training are not uncommon , and may even be the norm [ 16 ] .
label: case obl punct amod nsubj punct appos case nmod punct case amod cc conj nmod acl compound obj cop advmod root punct cc aux advmod cop det conj punct dep punct punct

text: Such a scenario may be found in different situations , including when one studies a language in a classroom and then stops taking classes [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] and when one is immersed in a foreign language setting and then moves away [ 19 ] .
label: det det nsubj aux aux root case amod obl punct case nmod nsubj advcl det obj case det obl cc advmod conj xcomp obj punct dep punct punct punct conj punct cc advmod nsubj aux conj case det amod compound obl cc advmod conj advmod punct dep punct punct

text: In the present study , we examine the outcomes of such a period of no exposure on the neurocognition of L2 grammar : that is , whether a substantial period of no exposure leads to decreased proficiency and / or less native - like neural processes ( “ use it or lose it ” [ 20 ] ) , no such changes , or perhaps whether even higher proficiency and / or more native - like processing may be observed .
label: case det amod obl punct nsubj root det obj case det det nmod case det nmod case det nmod case compound nmod punct advmod fixed punct mark det amod nsubj case det nmod parataxis case amod obl cc cc conj advmod compound punct amod amod conj punct punct parataxis obj cc conj obj punct punct dep punct punct punct det amod conj punct cc advmod mark advmod amod nsubj cc cc conj advmod compound punct amod conj aux aux conj punct

text: Additionally , we test whether any such outcomes might vary as a function of the type of L2 training , in particular between classroom - like and immersion - like contexts .
label: advmod punct nsubj root mark det amod nsubj aux ccomp case det obl case det nmod case compound nmod punct case nmod case compound punct amod cc compound punct conj obl punct

text: Previous Research
label: amod root

text: We are aware of six studies designed to investigate the effects of a substantial period of limited exposure following adult L2 training [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] , [ 21 ] – [ 24 ] , all of which were restricted to the examination of behavioral ( performance ) outcomes .
label: nsubj cop root case nummod obl acl mark advcl det obj case det amod nmod case amod nmod acl compound compound obj punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct case punct nmod punct punct nsubj case nmod aux acl case det obl case amod punct appos punct nmod punct

text: ( Note that we do not consider case studies , purely observational data , or research on L2s acquired by children ; for a comprehensive review , see [ 16 ] ) .
label: punct root mark nsubj aux advmod ccomp compound obj punct advmod amod conj punct cc conj case nmod acl case obl punct case det amod obl punct parataxis punct obj punct punct punct

text: The six studies tested L2 learners after periods of 1 month to 50 years of limited L2 exposure , mainly on general language skills [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] , [ 21 ] , [ 23 ] , [ 24 ] , though also on more specific paradigms meant to target aspects of grammatical abilities [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] or lexical abilities [ 22 ] , [ 23 ] .
label: det nummod nsubj root compound obj case obl case nummod nmod case nummod nmod case amod compound nmod punct advmod case amod compound obl punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct advmod advmod case advmod amod obl acl mark xcomp obj case amod nmod punct dep punct punct punct conj punct cc amod conj punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct

text: These language measures were compared in most studies to the same measures in a different set of subjects who had not experienced a period of limited exposure [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] , [ 22 ] , [ 23 ] , or to retrospective ratings of the same subjects [ 21 ] , with only one longitudinal study testing the same subjects before and after a period of limited exposure [ 24 ] .
label: det compound nsubj aux root case amod obl case det amod obl case det amod nmod case nmod nsubj aux advmod acl det obj case amod nmod punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct cc case amod conj case det amod nmod punct dep punct punct mark advmod nummod amod nsubj advcl det amod obj case cc conj det obl case amod nmod punct dep punct punct

text: Across the studies , the periods of limited exposure followed either classroom training [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] , [ 22 ] , [ 24 ] or mixed classroom and immersion training [ 21 ] , [ 23 ] , [ 24 ] .
label: case det obl punct det nsubj case amod nmod root cc compound obj punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct cc amod compound cc conj conj punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct

text: The training lasted varying lengths of time , apparently usually in the range of a few years , and resulted in seemingly varying proficiency levels ( though not directly measured , except by [ 24 ] ) prior to the period of limited exposure .
label: det nsubj root amod obl case nmod punct advmod advmod case det obl case det amod nmod punct cc conj case advmod amod compound obl punct mark advmod advmod acl punct mark case punct obl punct punct case fixed det obl case amod nmod punct

text: Overall , the results of the six studies have been taken to suggest the following .
label: advmod punct det nsubj case det nummod nmod aux aux root mark xcomp det obj punct

text: A period of limited exposure generally leads to attrition ( loss ) of L2 performance or knowledge [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] , [ 21 ] , [ 23 ] .
label: det nsubj case amod nmod advmod root case obl punct appos punct case compound nmod cc conj punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct

text: Such loss has been observed after as little as a few months of limited exposure , e.g. , after a 1 - 7 month [ 23 ] or 6 month delay [ 21 ] , as well as after 2 years [ 18 ] , though in one case it was observed only by 3 - 5 years , and not earlier [ 17 ] .
label: amod nsubj aux aux root case advmod obl case det amod obl case amod nmod punct advmod punct case det nummod case nmod compound punct dep punct cc nummod conj obl punct dep punct punct cc fixed fixed case nummod conj punct dep punct punct mark case nummod obl nsubj aux advcl advmod case nummod case nmod obl punct cc advmod conj punct dep punct punct

text: Although attrition may take place within the first few years , some studies suggest that it then appears to level off , with no further losses occurring [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] .
label: mark nsubj aux advcl obj case det amod amod obl punct det nsubj root mark nsubj advmod ccomp mark xcomp compound punct mark det amod nsubj advcl punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct

text: Higher levels of proficiency ( or exposure ) may be associated with less attrition [ 17 ] , [ 18 ] , [ 21 ] , [ 23 ] or even with no observed losses [ 21 ] .
label: amod nsubj case nmod punct cc conj punct aux aux root case amod obl punct dep punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct punct punct conj punct cc advmod case det amod conj punct dep punct punct

text: Moreover , one study found no changes at all in performance , across proficiency levels , after either 2 or 4 years of limited exposure [ 22 ] .
label: advmod punct nummod nsubj root det obj case obl case nmod punct case compound obl punct case cc nummod cc conj obl case amod nmod punct dep punct punct

text: Finally , in some cases a gain in performance has been observed : after 1.5 years of limited exposure in one study , particularly for L2 learners with immersion as well as classroom training [ 24 ] , and in another study after 2 years , though only for some abilities , such as listening and reading comprehension [ 18 ] .
label: advmod punct case det obl det nsubj case nmod aux aux root punct case nummod obl case amod nmod case nummod obl punct advmod case compound obl case nmod cc fixed fixed compound conj punct dep punct punct cc case det conj case nummod orphan punct advmod advmod case det orphan punct case fixed compound cc conj nmod punct dep punct punct

text: It remains unclear what might explain such gains , which have been attributed to motivation and to L2 experience during the period of ostensibly limited exposure [ 24 ] , or to factors related to general maturation , cognitive development , or continued academic training [ 18 ] .
label: expl root xcomp nsubj aux acl amod obj punct nsubj aux aux acl case obl cc case compound conj case det nmod case advmod amod nmod punct dep punct punct cc case conj acl case amod obl punct amod conj punct cc amod amod conj punct dep punct punct

text: Leading Dutch Librarians into DH
label: root amod obj case obl

text: Michiel Cock m.p.cock@vu.nl Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam , the Netherlands
label: root flat list list flat flat punct det list

text: Lotte Wilms lotte.wilms@kb.nl National Library of the Netherlands , the Netherlands
label: root flat list amod list case det nmod punct det list

text: In 2015 , an initiative was started to set up a Dutch speaking DH+Lib community in the Netherlands and Belgium , based on the example of the American communal space of librarians , archivists , LIS graduate students , and information specialists to discuss topics ‘ Where the Digital Humanities and Libraries meet ’ .
label: case obl punct det nsubj aux root mark advcl compound det compound amod compound obj case det obl cc conj punct advcl case det obl case det amod amod nmod case nmod punct conj punct compound compound conj punct cc compound conj mark advcl obj punct advmod det amod nsubj cc conj acl punct punct

text: At the initial meeting it became apparent that most participants were there to learn more about digital humanities and were not ( yet ) in the situation where they were able to offer expertise on the subject .
label: case det amod obl expl root xcomp mark amod nsubj cop csubj mark advcl obj case amod obl cc cop advmod punct advmod punct case det conj advmod nsubj cop acl mark xcomp obj case det nmod punct

text: On the administrative level , the directors of the libraries participating in the consortium of Dutch academic libraries ( UKB ) also expressed the wish that librarians become more fluent in DH .
label: case det amod obl punct det nsubj case det nmod acl case det obl case amod amod nmod punct appos punct advmod root det obj mark nsubj acl advmod xcomp case obl punct

text: A year later , the National Library of the Netherlands ( Koninklijke Bibliotheek ) , and the University Library of the Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam again concluded that librarians at their institutes who wanted to get involved in DH needed more training to adequately support researchers and students in this field .
label: det obl advmod punct det amod nsubj case det nmod punct compound appos punct punct cc det compound conj case det compound nmod nmod advmod root mark nsubj case nmod nmod nsubj acl mark aux xcomp case obl ccomp amod obj mark advmod advcl obj cc conj case det nmod punct

text: Therefore both institutes joined forces to develop a set of clinics on DH for librarians .
label: advmod det nsubj root obj mark advcl det obj case nmod case nmod case nmod punct

text: The two institutes were later joined by the Leiden University Libraries .
label: det nummod nsubj aux advmod root case det compound compound obl punct

text: We see this as the ideal opportunity to provide these educative sessions not only to our own librarians , but also to the academic librarians of other Dutch research libraries .
label: nsubj root obj case det amod obl mark acl det amod obj advmod advmod case nmod amod obl punct cc advmod case det amod conj case amod amod compound nmod punct

text: In essence , we want to teach our country ’s librarians the ins and outs of DH in order for them to take up their natural role of facilitating and supporting research and ideally become the research partner needed in DH projects .
label: case obl punct nsubj root mark xcomp nmod nmod case iobj det obj cc conj case nmod mark fixed mark nsubj mark advcl compound nmod amod obj mark acl cc conj obj cc advmod conj det compound xcomp acl case compound obl punct

text: The aim of these clinics is to provide basic methodological competencies and technical skills in DH , for a diverse group of librarians , consisting of both subject and technical librarians with basic technical skills .
label: det nsubj case det nmod cop mark root amod amod obj cc amod conj case nmod punct case det amod obl case nmod punct acl case cc compound cc conj obl case amod amod nmod punct

text: The content of these sessions should enable them to provide services to researchers and students , identify remaining gaps in knowledge or skills that they could address by self - directed learning and ( perhaps ) to automate their daily library work .
label: det nsubj case det nmod aux root obj mark xcomp obj case obl cc conj punct conj amod obj case nmod cc conj obj nsubj aux acl case compound punct amod obl cc punct advmod punct mark conj nmod amod compound obj punct

text: We are not setting out to turn them into programmers or data crunchers , but want to boost their knowledge level to where they feel comfortable providing information about DH projects , follow the literature and research , follow online tutorials and hopefully take up the challenge of finishing this professional development by engaging with the DH community .
label: nsubj aux advmod root compound mark xcomp obj case obl cc compound conj punct cc conj mark xcomp nmod compound obj case obl nsubj advcl xcomp advcl obj case compound nmod punct conj det obj cc conj punct conj amod obj cc advmod conj compound det obj mark acl det amod obj mark advcl case det compound obl punct

text: In order to design this curriculum we follow a four step approach with a Working Out Loud - principle ( Williams , 2010 ) :
label: mark fixed mark advcl det obj nsubj root det nummod compound obj case det compound advmod advmod punct nmod punct dep punct nmod punct punct

text: Desk research about what being a DH librarian entails ( e.g. Hartsell - Gundy et al. , 2015 ; Mulligan , 2016 ; also see the Zotero library of the LIBER Digital Humanities working group ) ;
label: compound root case nmod cop det compound csubj acl punct advmod dep punct flat cc conj punct nmod punct conj punct nmod punct advmod parataxis det compound obj case det compound amod compound amod nmod punct punct

text: Identify possible subjects , based on experience , a comparison of existing teaching material related to DH ( e.g. The Programming Historian , the Digital Scholarship Training Programme at the British Library and Columbia University 's Developing Librarian project ) and the TaDiRAH taxonomy of research activities ;
label: root amod obj punct advcl case obl punct det conj case amod compound nmod acl case obl punct advmod det amod appos punct det amod compound compound conj case det amod nmod cc compound nmod case amod compound conj punct cc det compound conj case compound nmod punct

text: Get feedback from researchers on possible subjects , based on the knowledge and skills they feel librarians need ;
label: root obj case nmod case amod nmod punct advcl case det obl cc conj nsubj acl nsubj ccomp punct

text: Get feedback from librarians on possible subjects , based on already known gaps in their knowledge and skills .
label: root obj case nmod case amod nmod punct advcl case advmod amod obl case nmod nmod cc conj punct

text: With these in hand , we will design the curriculum of clinics , based on the method of ' constructive alignment ' ( Biggs et al. , 2011 ) , to make sure that the intended learning objectives and the teaching / learning activities stay aligned .
label: mark nsubj case advcl punct nsubj aux root det obj case nmod punct advcl case det obl case punct amod nmod punct punct dep cc conj punct nmod punct punct mark advcl xcomp mark det amod compound nsubj cc det compound cc conj conj ccomp xcomp punct

text: Our plan is to organize a maximum of 6 clinics , each one full day .
label: nmod nsubj cop mark root det obj case nummod nmod punct nsubj nummod amod acl punct

text: Each day starts with one or more lectures by researchers , that address the conceptual knowledge needed .
label: det nsubj root case nummod cc conj obl case nmod punct nsubj acl det amod obj acl punct

text: The afternoon sessions will be devoted to the hands - on training of skills , following the Library Carpentry model as closely as possible .
label: det compound nsubj aux aux root case det compound punct amod obl case nmod punct acl det compound compound obj advmod advmod mark advcl punct

text: By having researchers provide the lecture sessions , we hope to fuel the enthusiasm of the librarians with the inspiration of direct contact with researchers and to provide access to a network within and across universities .
label: mark advcl obj xcomp det compound obj punct nsubj root mark xcomp det obj case det nmod case det obl case amod nmod case nmod cc mark conj obj case det nmod case cc conj nmod punct

text: With these clinics , we hope to initiate a stream of DH activities in Dutch universities , making access to support easier for new digital scholars .
label: case det obl punct nsubj root mark xcomp det obj case compound nmod case amod nmod punct advcl obj case nmod xcomp case amod amod obl punct

text: The poster at DH2017 will present the curriculum , its position in the international context and offer the lessons learned from both the design process and the first clinics .
label: det nsubj case nmod aux root det obj punct nmod conj case det amod nmod cc conj det obj acl case cc det compound obl cc det amod conj punct

text: We welcome discussion about our efforts and the possibilities of applying this in other contexts .
label: nsubj root obj case nmod nmod cc det conj mark acl obj case amod obl punct

text: Byron received his early formal education at Aberdeen Grammar School , and in August 1799 entered the school of Dr. William Glennie , in Dulwich . [ 17 ]
label: nsubj root nmod amod amod obj case compound compound nmod punct cc case obl nmod conj det obj case nmod flat flat punct case nmod punct punct dep punct

text: Placed under the care of a Dr. Bailey , he was encouraged to exercise in moderation but not restrain himself from " violent " bouts in an attempt to overcompensate for his deformed foot .
label: advcl case det obl case det nmod flat punct nsubj aux root mark xcomp case obl cc advmod conj obj case punct amod punct obl case det obl mark acl case nmod amod obl punct

text: His mother interfered with his studies , often withdrawing him from school , with the result that he lacked discipline and his classical studies were neglected .
label: nmod nsubj root case nmod obl punct advmod advcl obj case obl punct case det obl mark nsubj acl obj cc nmod amod nsubj aux conj punct

text: In 1801 , he was sent to Harrow , where he remained until July 1805 . [ 6 ]
label: case obl punct nsubj aux root case obl punct advmod nsubj acl case obl nmod punct punct dep punct

text: An undistinguished student and an unskilled cricketer , he did represent the school during the very first Eton v Harrow cricket match at Lord 's in 1805 . [ 19 ]
label: det amod advcl cc det amod conj punct nsubj aux root det obj case det advmod amod compound case nmod compound obl case obl case case obl punct punct dep punct

text: His lack of moderation was not restricted to physical exercise .
label: nmod nsubj case nmod aux advmod root case amod obl punct

text: Byron fell in love with Mary Chaworth , whom he met while at school , [ 6 ] and she was the reason he refused to return to Harrow in September 1803 .
label: nsubj root case obl case obl flat punct obj nsubj acl mark case advcl punct punct dep punct cc nsubj cop det conj nsubj acl mark xcomp case obl case obl nmod punct

text: His mother wrote , " He has no indisposition that I know of but love , desperate love , the worst of all maladies in my opinion . In short , the boy is distractedly in love with Miss Chaworth . " [ 6 ]
label: nmod nsubj root punct punct nsubj ccomp det obj obl nsubj acl case case nmod punct amod appos punct det appos case det obl case nmod obl punct case parataxis punct det nsubj cop advmod case parataxis case nmod flat punct punct punct dep punct

text: In Byron 's later memoirs , " Mary Chaworth is portrayed as the first object of his adult sexual feelings . " [ 20 ]
label: case nmod case amod obl punct punct nsubj flat aux root case det amod obl case nmod amod amod nmod punct punct punct dep punct

text: Byron finally returned in January 1804 , [ 6 ] to a more settled period which saw the formation of a circle of emotional involvements with other Harrow boys , which he recalled with great vividness : " My school friendships were with me passions ( for I was always violent ) . " [ 21 ]
label: nsubj advmod root case obl nmod punct punct dep punct case det advmod amod obl nsubj acl det obj case det nmod case amod nmod case amod compound nmod punct obj nsubj acl case amod obl punct punct nmod compound nsubj cop case nmod parataxis punct mark nsubj cop advmod advcl punct punct punct punct dep punct

text: His nostalgic poems about his Harrow friendships , Childish Recollections ( 1806 ) , express a prescient " consciousness of sexual differences that may in the end make England untenable to him . " [ 23 ]
label: nmod amod nsubj case nmod compound nmod punct amod appos punct nmod punct punct root det amod punct obj case amod nmod nsubj aux case det obl acl obj xcomp case obl punct punct punct dep punct

text: Joshua Abraham Norton ( c. 1818 – January 8 , 1880 ) , known as Emperor Norton , was a citizen of San Francisco , California , who in 1859 proclaimed himself " Norton I , Emperor of the United States " .
label: nsubj flat flat punct advmod nmod case nmod nmod punct nmod punct punct acl case obl flat punct cop det root case nmod flat punct appos punct nsubj case obl acl obj punct xcomp dep punct appos case det amod nmod punct punct

label: mark nsubj advcl det obj case obl nsubj acl mark xcomp nmod compound obj punct nmod case amod nsubj root punct

text: Friday , May 8 , 2009

"

text: Australian children suffering from iodine deficiency
label: amod nsubj root case compound obl

text: Thursday , February 23 , 2006
label: root punct compound appos punct nmod

text: Almost half of all Australian primary school children are mild to moderately iodine deficient , researchers say .
label: advmod nsubj case det amod amod compound nmod cop advmod case obl obl ccomp punct nsubj root punct

text: A new study documenting iodine nutritional status in Australian school children has revealed many are not getting enough iodine - which can lead to mental and growth retardation .
label: det amod nsubj acl compound amod obj case amod compound nmod aux root nsubj aux advmod ccomp amod obj punct nsubj aux advcl case amod cc conj obl punct

text: The report 's authors say iodine deficiency is " the sleeper health issue in Australia " , and potentially a very serious one .
label: det nmod case nsubj root compound nsubj cop punct det compound compound ccomp case nmod punct punct cc advmod det advmod amod conj punct

text: The results of the Australian National Iodine Nutrition Study published in the Medical Journal of Australia this week , revealed that children in mainland Australia are borderline iodine deficient .
label: det nsubj case det amod amod compound compound nmod acl case det amod obl case nmod det obl punct root mark nsubj case compound nmod cop advmod compound ccomp punct

text: The report has prompted calls for all edible salt to be iodised .
label: det nsubj aux root obj mark det amod nsubj mark aux advcl punct

text: They say adding the mineral to salt is the simplest and most effective method of preventing iodine deficiency disorders .
label: nsubj root csubj det obj case obl cop det amod cc advmod conj ccomp mark acl compound compound obj punct

text: A cross-sectional survey of 1709 schoolchildren - aged 8 – 10 years , from 88 schools - was carried out in New South Wales , Victoria , South Australia , Western Australia and Queensland , between July 2003 and December 2004 .
label: det amod nsubj case nummod nmod punct amod nummod case nmod obl punct case nummod nmod punct aux root compound case compound compound obl punct conj punct compound conj punct amod conj cc conj punct case obl nmod cc conj nmod punct

text: Tasmania was excluded from the study - where an voluntary iodine fortification program using iodised salt in bread , is ongoing .
label: nsubj aux root case det obl punct advmod det amod compound compound nsubj acl amod obj case nmod punct cop acl punct

text: The authors say the results confirm the existence of inadequate iodine intake in the Australian population .
label: det nsubj root det nsubj ccomp det obj case amod compound nmod case det amod nmod punct

text: They call for " urgent implementation of mandatory iodisation of all edible salt in Australia . "
label: nsubj root case punct amod obl case amod nmod case det amod nmod case nmod punct punct

text: Most iodine in food comes from seafood , milk and iodised salt .
label: amod nsubj case nmod root case obl punct conj cc amod conj punct

text: Professor Cres Eastman , Director of the National Iodine Nutrition study , and Chairman of the Australian Centre for Control of Iodine Deficiency Disorders , says it is crucial that children and pregnant women in particular have an adequate intake of iodine .
label: nsubj flat flat punct appos case det amod compound compound nmod punct cc conj case det amod nmod case nmod case compound compound nmod punct root expl cop ccomp mark nsubj cc amod conj case nmod csubj det amod obj case nmod punct

text: Iodine deficiency can lead to serious health problems including brain damage , stunted growth and deafness .
label: compound nsubj aux root case amod compound obl case compound nmod punct amod conj cc conj punct

text: Professor Eastman says manufacturers could easily remedy the situation by using iodised salt in their products in line with the United States and most European countries .
label: nsubj flat root nsubj aux advmod ccomp det obj mark advcl amod obj case nmod obl case obl case det amod nmod cc amod amod conj punct

text: " I suspect they wo n't do that on a voluntary basis , we 've tried so far and have n't succeeded , so we 've convinced the Food Standards of Australia and New Zealand | that all salt should be iodised , " he said .
label: punct nsubj ccomp nsubj aux advmod ccomp obj case det amod obl punct nsubj aux parataxis advmod advmod cc aux advmod conj punct advmod nsubj aux parataxis det compound iobj case nmod cc conj flat punct mark det nsubj aux aux ccomp punct punct nsubj root punct

text: The report says the decline in iodine intake appears to be due to changes in the dairy industry , where chlorine - containing sanitisers have replaced iodine - containing sanitisers .
label: det nsubj root det nsubj case compound nmod ccomp mark cop case fixed xcomp case det compound nmod punct advmod compound punct amod nsubj aux acl compound punct amod obj punct

text: Iodine released from these chemicals into milk has been the major source of dietary iodine in Australia for at least four decades , but is now declining .
label: nsubj acl case det obl case obl aux cop det amod root case amod nmod case obl case advmod fixed nummod obl punct cc aux advmod conj punct

text: Another contributory factor has been the decreasing consumption of iodised salt used in foods .
label: det amod nsubj aux cop det amod root case amod nmod acl case obl punct

text: The report states that few if any food manufacturers use iodised salt in the preparation and manufacture of foods .
label: det nsubj root mark amod mark advcl compound nsubj ccomp amod obj case det obl cc conj case nmod punct

text: Professor Eastman says iodine is added to only 10 per cent of Australian salt in contravention of a World Health Organisation recommendation that all salt be iodised .
label: nsubj flat root nsubj aux ccomp case advmod nummod obl goeswith case amod nmod case obl case det compound compound compound nmod mark det nsubj aux acl punct

text: He says authorities are reacting slowly to his urgent calls for mandatory iodised salt .
label: nsubj root nsubj aux ccomp advmod case nmod amod obl case amod amod nmod punct

text: " The effects of iodine deficiency are dependent upon how severe it is and when it occurs .
label: punct det nsubj case compound nmod cop root case advmod obl nsubj advcl cc conj nsubj advcl punct

text: 1.1 What is Government ?

text: DIFFERENT TYPES OF GOVERNMENT

text: The government of the United States can best be described as a republic , or representative democracy .

text: A democracy is a government in which political power — influence over institutions , leaders , and policies — rests in the hands of the people .

text: Instead , they elect representatives to make decisions and pass laws on behalf of all the people .

text: Thus , U.S. citizens vote for members of Congress , the president and vice president , members of state legislatures , governors , mayors , and members of town councils and school boards to act on their behalf .

text: Most representative governments favor majority rule :

text: the opinions of the majority of the people have more influence with government than those of the minority .

text: However , in representative governments like the United States , minority rights are protected : people can not be deprived of certain rights even if an overwhelming number of people think that they should be .

text: Because decisions are made through majority rule , making your opinions known and voting for those men and women who make decisions that affect all of us are critical and influential forms of civic engagement in a representative democracy such as the United States .

text: In a direct democracy , unlike representative democracy , people participate directly in making government decisions .

text: For example , in ancient Athens , the most famous example of a direct democracy , all male citizens were allowed to attend meetings of the Assembly .

text: Although neither the federal government nor any of the state governments function as a direct democracy — the Constitution requires the national and state governments to be representative forms of government — some elements of direct democracy do exist in the United States .

text: While residents of the different states vote for people to represent them and to make laws in their behalf in the state legislatures and in Congress , people may still directly vote on certain issues .

text: Why the Division of Labor Increases Production
label: root det nsubj case nmod advcl obj

text: When we divide and subdivide the tasks involved with producing a good or service , workers and businesses can produce a greater quantity of output .
label: advmod nsubj advcl cc conj det obj acl mark advcl det obj cc conj punct nsubj cc conj aux root det amod obj case nmod punct

text: In his observations of pin factories , Smith noticed that one worker alone might make 20 pins in a day , but that a small business of 10 workers ( some of whom would need to complete two or three of the 18 tasks involved with pin - making ) , could make 48,000 pins in a day .
label: case nmod obl case compound nmod punct nsubj root mark nummod nsubj advmod aux ccomp nummod obj case det obl punct cc mark det amod nsubj case nummod nmod punct nsubj case nmod aux acl mark xcomp obj cc conj case det nummod nmod acl case compound punct obl punct punct aux conj nummod obj case det obl punct

text: How can a group of workers , each specializing in certain tasks , produce so much more than the same number of workers who try to produce the entire good or service by themselves ?
label: advmod aux det nsubj case nmod punct nsubj acl case amod obl punct root advmod advmod obj case det amod obl case nmod nsubj acl mark xcomp det amod obj cc conj case obl punct

text: Smith offered three reasons .
label: nsubj root nummod obj punct

text: First , specialization in a particular small job allows workers to focus on the parts of the production process where they have an advantage .
label: advmod punct nsubj case det amod amod nmod root iobj mark xcomp case det obl case det compound nmod advmod nsubj acl det obj punct

text: ( In later chapters , we will develop this idea by discussing comparative advantage . )
label: punct case amod obl punct nsubj aux root det obj mark advcl amod obj punct punct

text: People have different skills , talents , and interests , so they will be better at some jobs than at others .
label: nsubj root amod obj punct conj punct cc conj punct advmod nsubj aux cop parataxis case det obl mark case advcl punct

text: The particular advantages may be based on educational choices , which are in turn shaped by interests and talents .
label: det amod nsubj aux aux root case amod obl punct nsubj aux case obl acl case obl cc conj punct

text: Only those with medical degrees qualify to become doctors , for instance .
label: advmod nsubj case amod nmod root mark xcomp xcomp punct case obl punct

text: For some goods , geography affects specialization .
label: case det obl punct nsubj root obj punct

text: For example , it is easier to be a wheat farmer in North Dakota than in Florida , but easier to run a tourist hotel in Florida than in North Dakota .
label: case obl punct expl cop root mark cop det compound csubj case compound obl mark case advcl punct cc conj mark xcomp det compound obj case obl mark case compound advcl punct

text: If you live in or near a big city , it is easier to attract enough customers to operate a successful dry cleaning business or movie theater than if you live in a sparsely populated rural area .
label: mark nsubj advcl case cc conj det amod obl punct expl cop root mark csubj amod obj mark acl det amod amod compound obj cc compound conj mark mark nsubj advcl case det advmod amod amod obl punct

text: Whatever the reason , if people specialize in the production of what they do best , they will be more effective than if they produce a combination of things , some of which they are good at and some of which they are not .
label: advcl det nsubj punct mark nsubj advcl case det obl case nmod nsubj acl advmod punct nsubj aux cop advmod root mark mark nsubj advcl det obj case nmod punct obl case nmod nsubj cop acl case cc orphan case nmod conj orphan orphan punct

text: Second , workers who specialize in certain tasks often learn to produce more quickly and with higher quality .
label: advmod punct nsubj nsubj acl case amod obl advmod root mark xcomp advmod advmod cc case amod conj punct

text: This pattern holds true for many workers , including assembly line laborers who build cars , stylists who cut hair , and doctors who perform heart surgery .
label: det nsubj root xcomp case amod obl punct case compound compound nmod nsubj acl obj punct conj nsubj acl obj punct cc conj nsubj acl compound obj punct

text: In fact , specialized workers often know their jobs well enough to suggest innovative ways to do their work faster and better .
label: case obl punct amod nsubj advmod root nmod obj advmod advmod mark advcl amod obj mark acl nmod obj advmod cc conj punct

text: A similar pattern often operates within businesses .
label: det amod nsubj advmod root case obl punct

text: In many cases , a business that focuses on one or a few products ( sometimes called its “ core competency ” ) is more successful than firms that try to make a wide range of products .
label: case amod obl punct det nsubj nsubj acl case nummod cc orphan conj obl punct advmod acl nmod punct amod xcomp punct punct cop advmod root case obl nsubj acl mark xcomp det amod obj case nmod punct

text: Third , specialization allows businesses to take advantage of economies of scale , which means that for many goods , as the level of production increases , the average cost of producing each individual unit declines .
label: advmod punct nsubj root iobj mark xcomp obj case nmod case nmod punct nsubj acl mark case amod obl punct mark det nsubj case nmod advcl punct det amod nsubj mark acl det amod obj ccomp punct

text: For example , if a factory produces only 100 cars per year , each car will be quite expensive to make on average .
label: case obl punct mark det nsubj advcl advmod nummod obj case obl punct det nsubj aux cop advmod root mark acl case obl punct

text: However , if a factory produces 50,000 cars each year , then it can set up an assembly line with huge machines and workers performing specialized tasks , and the average cost of production per car will be lower .
label: advmod punct mark det nsubj advcl nummod obj det obl punct advmod nsubj aux root compound det compound obj case amod nmod cc conj acl amod obj punct cc det amod nsubj case nmod case nmod aux cop conj punct

text: The ultimate result of workers who can focus on their preferences and talents , learn to do their specialized jobs better , and work in larger organizations is that society as a whole can produce and consume far more than if each person tried to produce all of his or her own goods and services .
label: det amod nsubj case nmod nsubj aux acl case nmod obl cc conj punct conj mark xcomp nmod amod obj advmod punct cc conj case amod obl cop mark nsubj case det nmod aux root cc conj advmod obj mark mark det nsubj advcl mark xcomp obj case nmod cc conj amod nmod cc conj punct

text: The division and specialization of labor has been a force against the problem of scarcity .

text: Everyone ’s an individual , so there are no hard and fast rules .

text: But , unless you personally know the members of your audience , here are some good rules of thumb to follow :

text: elderly people wo n’t like crude jokes ;
